<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-15T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-15T11:00:00-05:00" n="354" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d354">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6081:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Fish</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-15T18:00:00+02:00">October 15, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received October 15—4:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>246. I attended a luncheon at the British Embassy today given in
                                honor of Anthony Eden<note n="15" xml:id="d354fn15">British
                                    Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs.</note> who told me he
                                left London Saturday and arrived yesterday. I gathered that the main
                                reason Eden’s visit was to conduct a personal inspection of the
                                defenses of Egypt and the Sudan, but it seems likely that he may
                                also take the occasion to seek to effect an improvement in
                                Anglo-Egyptian relations particularly as regards the attitude of the
                                King by whom Eden said he was being received.</p>
                            <p>The Ambassador told me that no reference to Eden’s visit was being
                                permitted in the press.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>